The Cherubim and Seraphim Movement Church, Surulere District, Lagos, yesterday held its Christmas carol of nine lessons with the theme: ‘Christ, the hope of a new beginning.’ In his message, the District Chairman, Prophet Sunday Korode, said despite the socio-economic turbulence facing the nation, God should be praised at this time. He described the carol as a service of Christian worship traditionally celebrated on or near Christmas. The guest minister, Archbishop of South-West and Bishop, Diocese of Ijebu, Methodist Church, Most Revd. M.O. Dare hinged the period of Christmas on not just merriment but a time for sober reflection to turn around and embrace a new life through Jesus Christ, the saviour of the world.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .